If you have 8 spare minutes and looking for something to watch hit the link in my bio to view some fun moments from the past 10 days in Hawaii. Featuring a fun session at Haleiwa with @rissmoore10 & @caroline_markss  with a few incredible waves from @griffin_cola @crosbycola & @ethan_ewing . A fun and challenging Coco head hike, and some hilarious tennis moments with the Aussies. 
Enjoy 🙌

Hey Guys, 

Last week I was fortunate enough to compete in the Super Girl Pro held at Oceanside Pier. It was exciting to get the jersey back on and surf a few heats. I hope you enjoy this light-hearted behind the scenes mini-VLOG. 

Keep the  questions coming and stay tuned for my Tahiti VLOG to drop next week.

Hey Guys, 

I've been spending my time in San Clemente lately where I've  utilised the @murfelectricbike program, endless amount of  waves  and delicious coffee's. Thanks for this  weeks question; What is your favourite  Coffee order? Hope this gives you an insight. 

Keep  sending  in  your questions and I  will try and give you  an answer in my future Mini-VLOG series. 

Stoked on having my new Hero 9 @gopro to capture the fun🤗

LP

node.text: Super happy to take part in the #StayLocal campaign the @WSL has help put together for us. It’s hard to know exactly how to help during this time but I know supporting local businesses is a huge part of it. Tom and I have chosen a few small businesses from both our home towns to support and the WSL is going to match our purchase. Hope everyone is staying healthy and continues to be kind to each other during this time. Remember to support your local businesses whenever you can. 💛 @aframesurfshop @handlebarcoffee @swell_cafe

node.text: Really wish I could say next week I’ll be doing this again… but unfortunately,  my body just isn’t ready to compete again quite yet. My team and I have made the decision to not compete in Mexico… I just want to say a huge thank you to all of my sponsors and the @wsl for the continued support throughout this injury. I promise I’m doing everything possible to come back soon and at 100%. But ultimately my body will tell me when I’m ready and I can’t force it. Thanks again everyone and I’ll be back soon!
